## Semantic Colors (Shadcn)

Use these for theme-aware elements: `background`, `foreground`, `card`, `muted-foreground`, `border`, `destructive`, `accent`.

## Typography

- **Font**: Inter (loaded via `next/font/google`, variable `--font-inter`)
- **H1**: `text-5xl sm:text-6xl lg:text-[72px]`, `font-bold`, `tracking-tight`
- **H2 (section)**: `text-3xl lg:text-4xl`, `font-bold`
- **H2 (subtitle)**: `text-3xl sm:text-4xl lg:text-[48px]`, `font-medium`
- **H3**: `text-xl`, `font-bold`
- **Body**: `text-base`, `leading-relaxed`, color `text-body`
- **Body large**: `text-lg sm:text-xl`, `leading-[32.5px]`
- **Small/tags**: `text-xs`, `font-medium`
- **Status badge**: `text-xs`, `font-semibold`, `uppercase`, `tracking-wider`

## Rules

- Never use raw hex colors inline; always use the Tailwind token classes
- The `amber` color is reserved exclusively for the "AWS" brand highlight
- Tech tags always use: `rounded border border-white-5 bg-white-5 px-2 py-1 text-xs font-medium text-text-tag`
- Section headings use a cyan bar prefix: `<div className="h-[2px] w-8 bg-cyan" />`
